<P>THE OFFICE OF CONSTABLE: BEING AN ENTIRELY NEW COMPENDIUM OF THE LAW CONCERNING THAT ANCIENT MINISTER FOR THE CONSERVATION OF THE PEACE.</P>
<P>CAREFULLY COMPILED FROM THE BEST AUTHORITIES.</P>
<P>WITH A PREFACE; AND AN INTRODUCTION, CONTAINING SOME ACCOUNT OF THE ORIGIN AND ANTIQUITY OF THE OFFICE.</P>
<P>LONDON: PRINTED FOR WHIELDON AND BUTTERWORTH, FLEET-STREET.</P>
<P>M.DCC.XCI.</P>
