<DIV1 TYPE="note">
<PB REF="151">
<HEAD>ADVERTISEMENT.</HEAD>
<P>ALL the books, rolls, and other muniments of the Savoy Court, anterior to the year 1683, are &s;up|po&s;ed to have peri&s;hed in private hands. But there is &s;uf|ficient evidence that the court has been regularly held ever &s;ince the acce&s;&s;ion of King Henry the Fourth, <HI>anno</HI> 1399; as, without doubt, it was long before that period; the Liberty being one of the olde&s;t in the kingdom, and having been parcel of the po&s;&s;e&s;&s;ions of the Duchy of Lanca&s;ter from the time of its fir&s;t erection, and even the property of he Earls of that title for near a century before.</P>
